[The
Tsukihi Spring Rite
]

This may have been a rite dedicated to the kami of the Mikushige Hall (
Mikushigedono
). This location was in the Jōgan Hall where the female royal secretaries (
nyokurōdo
) and others worked at sewing clothing. This kami may have been a kami of the Wardrobe Bureau.

[The

 Garden Kami (

  sono no kami

 ) Rite

]

       [For the

        Sacred Meal
								with the Kami in the Sixth and Twelfth Months (

         Kan'imake

        )

       ]

From the establishment of the ritsuryō system, the Great Harvest Rite was performed in the eleventh month over a two day period. In the afternoon, the officials conducted a large ceremony to present offerings (
hanpei
) to 304 kami at designated shrines throughout the Kinai. The Great Harvest Rite was held on a tiger day, when the sovereign consumed the newly harvested grains, as well as the foods listed here, and communed with the kami.

The Seven Royal Banquets were banquets attended by his majesty (
sechie
): New Year's Royal Banquet, White Horse Royal Banquet, Song and Dance Royal Banquet, Fifth Day Royal Banquet, Seventh Month Seventh Day Royal Banquet, Double Yang Banquet, and the Warmth of Sake Royal Banquet.

