[
Ninth Month Ninth Day [Double Yang] Royal Banquet
]

The Plating Station (
Morimono dokoro
) was where food was arranged on the correct tableware before being carried to diners. The Offerings Station (
Shinmotsu dokoro
) aided in food preparation. It is important to distinguish these stations, as they represent two types. The Offerings Station was a relatively stable bureaucratic unit with a designated head, who was a noble of sufficient rank to enter the sovereign's living quarters. The Palace Kitchen (
Mizushi dokoro
) was another station in this category. However, the Plating Station was a temporary space set-up for an event with workers assigned for the occasion.

