grinding salt and elm
, 2 for grinding flour〉; 8 pestles 〈for grinding various things〉; 5 winnows 〈2 for separating salt and elm, 3 are for winnowing rice flour〉; 190 dried gourds 〈for ladling various liquids〉;

div.note:
Ground elm bark (
nire
) when combined with salt functioned as a preservative that inhibited the growth of certain bacteria. Glutamic acid may also lend the salt-pickles a more complex flavor.

