div.note:
[For the Red Label of Approval (

 shime no ake no hata

)]

This red banner of approval is a literal translation of the characters used. This cloth was marked with a seal. In the ninth and tenth centuries, the red banner came to function as a purifying force for those involved in tribute for the sovereign's meals as fears arose around pollution (
kegare
) in the food's production and sourcing.

